.TH ARCHFS 4
.SH NAME
archfs \- mount mkfs-style archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B archfs
[
.B -abcC
]
[
.B -m 
.I mtpt
]
.I archfile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Archfs
mounts at
.I mtpt
(default
.BR /mnt/arch )
a file system presenting the contents of an 
archive in the format produced by
the
.B -a
flag to
.IR mkfs (8).
The
.BR -a ,
.BR -b ,
.BR -c ,
and
.B -C
flags control the flag argument
to the
.B mount
system call
(see
.IR bind (2))
as in the
.B mount
command
(see
.IR bind (1)).
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/archfs.c
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR mkfs (8)
